<br>
From skill level 1, rogue Hide is both Inviz and Inviz to Undead at the same time.<br>
<br>
This guy however sees though Hide. I remember Yalum saying that he would be sitting at window sneaking and hid and as soon as the Servant popped, he aggro'd him.<br>
<br>
I fought him at 53 and it was close. I had a cleric friend there and she did toss one heal on me. But without that, it I had tried to solo it and me not using my ID or Poison or my Locusture I would have lost. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unightgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NightGod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 9:39:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3984.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Locked Door in Katta</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hide max is 200 as well as sneak. Some undead mobs can make you some can't. You have to learn which.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
